<h2>More Than Curb Appeal: The Practical Benefits of Edging</h2>
<p>A clean edge is about more than just aesthetics. It creates a vital root barrier, preventing aggressive turfgrasses from creeping into your flower beds, garden plots, and mulched areas. This simple line in the soil saves you hours of weeding.<br/><br/>Furthermore, proper edging protects your investment in hardscapes. By keeping grass and soil contained, you prevent root systems from undermining and cracking your Chicago driveways, walkways, and patios, which are already under stress from our seasonal freeze-thaw cycles.</p>

<h2>The King Coleman Process for Flawless Lawn Lines</h2>
<p>Achieving a perfect edge requires professional-grade equipment and a systematic approach. As a general contractor focused on detail, we bring the same precision to our lawn maintenance services as we do to a full home renovation.</p>

<h2>Initial Assessment</h2>
<p>Our process begins by walking your property to define the borders between your lawn and all hardscapes (curbs, sidewalks, driveways) and softscapes (flower beds). We identify and mark any potential obstacles like sprinkler heads or utility lines.</p>

